---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Pipeline from '../components/Pipeline.astro';
---
<Base title="ARIA - AI Representation for Instruction Architecture">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-20 pb-16 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="font-mono text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold text-accent tracking-wider mb-4">ARIA</h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-muted mb-2">AI Representation for Instruction Architecture</p>
      <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium mt-8 mb-12 leading-snug">
        The AI composes. The machine performs.<br class="hidden sm:block" />
        <span class="text-muted">The human is the audience.</span>
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center mb-16">
        <a href="/get-started" class="px-8 py-3 bg-accent text-bg font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-accent-hover transition-colors">Get Started</a>
        <a href="/story" class="px-8 py-3 border border-border text-text rounded-lg hover:border-muted transition-colors">Read the Story</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Hero code block -->
      <div class="text-left max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-code-bg border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <div class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-border flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-[#ff5f57]"></span>
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-[#febc2e]"></span>
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-[#28c840]"></span>
            <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-muted font-mono">hello.aria</span>
          </div>
          <pre class="!border-0 !rounded-none !m-0"><code class="text-sm leading-relaxed"><span class="text-muted">(</span><span class="text-[#ff7b72]">module</span> <span class="text-[#a5d6ff]">"hello"</span>
  <span class="text-muted">(</span><span class="text-[#ff7b72]">func</span> <span class="text-accent">$greet</span>
    <span class="text-muted">(</span><span class="text-[#d2a8ff]">param</span> <span class="text-accent">$name</span> <span class="text-[#79c0ff]">str</span><span class="text-muted">)</span> <span class="text-muted">(</span><span class="text-[#d2a8ff]">result</span> <span class="text-[#79c0ff]">str</span><span class="text-muted">)</span>
    <span class="text-muted">(</span><span class="text-[#d2a8ff]">effects</span> <span class="text-[#7ee787]">pure</span><span class="text-muted">)</span>
    <span class="text-muted">(</span><span class="text-[#d2a8ff]">intent</span> <span class="text-[#a5d6ff]">"Greet a user by name"</span><span class="text-muted">)</span>
    <span class="text-muted">(</span><span class="text-[#ff7b72]">return</span> <span class="text-muted">(</span><span class="text-[#79c0ff]">concat.str</span> <span class="text-[#a5d6ff]">"Hello, "</span> <span class="text-accent">$name</span><span class="text-muted">))))</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pipeline -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-center text-lg font-medium text-muted mb-8">The Pipeline</h2>
      <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
        <Pipeline />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Clojure -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Why Clojure</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          ARIA-IR is s-expressions. Clojure is s-expressions. The toolchain that parses one should be written in the other. The parser collapses to <code>read-string</code> plus validation. This is not a coincidence. It is the right choice.
        </p>
        <p>
          Clojure runs on the JVM. The toolchain is portable to every platform Java runs on. No native compilation step, no platform-specific builds. A single uberjar runs everywhere.
        </p>
        <p>
          Clojure's immutable data structures mirror SSA semantics. An ARIA-IR program is a value. Transforming it produces a new value. The compiler pipeline is a sequence of pure functions over immutable data. The language and the problem fit like a key in a lock.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Elevator pitch -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-8 text-center">
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium leading-relaxed">
        Human-readable programming languages were designed for human authors. If AI is writing the code and a compiler is consuming it, the intermediate representation should be optimized for that pipeline.
      </p>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium text-accent leading-relaxed">
        ARIA is that representation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GitHub CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center">
      <a href="https://github.com/jhavera/aria-clj" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
         class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-8 py-4 bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl hover:border-accent transition-colors">
        <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 0C5.37 0 0 5.37 0 12c0 5.31 3.435 9.795 8.205 11.385.6.105.825-.255.825-.57 0-.285-.015-1.23-.015-2.235-3.015.555-3.795-.735-4.035-1.41-.135-.345-.72-1.41-1.23-1.695-.42-.225-1.02-.78-.015-.795.945-.015 1.62.87 1.845 1.23 1.08 1.815 2.805 1.305 3.495.99.105-.78.42-1.305.765-1.605-2.67-.3-5.46-1.335-5.46-5.925 0-1.305.465-2.385 1.23-3.225-.12-.3-.54-1.53.12-3.18 0 0 1.005-.315 3.3 1.23.96-.27 1.98-.405 3-.405s2.04.135 3 .405c2.295-1.56 3.3-1.23 3.3-1.23.66 1.65.24 2.88.12 3.18.765.84 1.23 1.905 1.23 3.225 0 4.605-2.805 5.625-5.475 5.925.435.375.81 1.095.81 2.22 0 1.605-.015 2.895-.015 3.3 0 .315.225.69.825.57A12.02 12.02 0 0 0 24 12c0-6.63-5.37-12-12-12z"/></svg>
        <span class="font-mono font-semibold">jhavera/aria-clj</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
